newsitem.title: USA: No bids on $2.02 mln Lakeville, Minn. - adviser.
newsitem.headline: No bids on $2.02 mln Lakeville, Minn. - adviser.

text.p: No bids were received on a $2.02 million Lakeville, Minn., general obligation improvement refunding bond issue which had been slated for competitive sale at 1400 EDT, the issuer's financial adviser said Monday.
The offering was auctioned at 1400 EDT, said Springsted Inc, but no bids were received. The adviser did not provide an explanation.
Two other Lakeville offerings - a $13 million issue and a $2.2 million issue - were sold through competitive auction.
